PtolC NEWS — user-visible changes by release

See CHANGELOG.md in the repository root for full detail.

Version 1.115 (2026-05-17)
  * Vowel filter: token_accept() for prose/markup/doc now rejects any
    token with no a/e/i/o/u vowels (consonant-only strings like "ydrx",
    "wlvf", etc.) and any token ending in a trailing apostrophe.
    Tokens ≥ 6 chars with vowel ratio < 15% are also rejected.
    This fixes monad_speak() surface output on post-Documents fields.
  * corpora/english_grammar.txt: 5 000-word seed corpus covering all
    English function words in natural prose sentences.
  * make grammar: ingests the grammar seed after make corpus.
    Correct ingest order: make corpus → make grammar → ptolemy -I <dir>.
  * fresh_start.sh: fixed sys.argv bug that caused IndexError when
    extracting stats from the assessment JSON for the README block.

Version 1.114 (2026-05-17)
  * -W <prompt>: Wick-rotated speak mode.  Applies σ → iσ to the Noether
    current: J_wick = β × E² × sin(σ·E).  Selects words by the imaginary
    (oscillatory) component of the field.  Run alongside -h to measure
    the divergence between real and imaginary Noether currents.
  * monad_speak_wick() added to monad.c / monad.h.

Version 1.113 (2026-05-17)
  * monad_speak() output filtered through token_accept(NS_FT_PROSE):
    consonant clusters, apostrophe fragments, and hex strings are now
    skipped in responses.  Internal field topology unchanged.
  * monad_English.bin: clean WordNet-only baseline released.
    14,164 vocab / 766,027 A-edges / deepest word: "philadelphos".

Version 1.112 (2026-05-16)
  * Auto-assessment: after every -I ingest, ptolemy runs eval_checkpoint.py
    on the saved checkpoint and writes <checkpoint>.assessment.json.
    Locates the script via $SMMIP_REPO or ~/Projects/Ptol/SMMIP/tools/.
  * Bug fix: ptolemy -s without -c now loads ~/.ptolemy/monad_wordnet.bin
    correctly.
  * Version and usage strings updated to "RedBlue Geometries Engine".
  * PtolC/TODO added (GNU-standard open work items).

Version 1.111 (2026-05-16)
  * Learn-time token filter: per-filetype rules (prose/code/markup/doc)
    reject numeric, UUID, hex, base64, long-caps, and overlength tokens
    silently; count visible in -F field health report.
  * Filesystem ingest: -I <path> walks a directory tree, dispatches
    to pdftotext/catdoc/pandoc/libxml2 by extension, honours .ptolemyignore,
    saves checkpoint every 500 files.
  * Daemon mode: -d starts a resident monad over a Unix domain socket;
    -D <query> sends a query to a running daemon.  Systemd socket
    activation supported without libsystemd.
  * Field health: -F prints beta distribution, field entropy, top A-edges,
    vocabulary coverage, pollution indicators, and rejection count.
  * Checkpoint v2: VocabEntry carries home_stratum and gen_stratum
    (NS_SIGMA_* constants from the Dixon tower).  v1 checkpoints load
    without modification.
  * PEM guard: monad_learn() refuses text beginning with "-----BEGIN ".
  * CMakeLists.txt added alongside Makefile.
  * Man pages: ptolemy(1), ptolemyignore(5).
  * Systemd user units: ptolemy.socket, ptolemy.service.
  * Logging: 4-hour rotating slots in ~/.ptolemy/logs/, 30-day GC.

Version 1.0 (2026-05-16)
  * Initial release.  learn (-l), hear/speak (-h), status (-s),
    word lookup (-w), verbosity levels, checkpoint v1, make corpus target.
